docs.abstract: Nvidia, Intel and Qualcomm are campaigning to protect their businesses before further crackdowns on the sale of semiconductor technology to Beijing.
docs.snippet: Nvidia, Intel and Qualcomm are campaigning to protect their businesses before further crackdowns on the sale of semiconductor technology to Beijing.
docs.lead_paragraph: A year after the Biden administration took its first major step toward restricting the sale of semiconductors to China, it has begun drafting additional limits aimed at denying Beijing the technology critical to modern-day weapons.

headline.main: How the Big Chip Makers Are Pushing Back on Biden’s China Agenda
headline.print_headline: Big Chip Makers Push Back on Biden’s Limits on Sale of Semiconductors to China

byline.original: By Tripp Mickle, David McCabe and Ana Swanson

docs.abstract: Behind the scenes, the technology relies on thousands of specialized computer chips.
docs.snippet: Behind the scenes, the technology relies on thousands of specialized computer chips.
docs.lead_paragraph: OpenAI’s ChatGPT exploded onto the scene nearly a year ago, reaching an estimated 100 million users in two months and setting off an A.I. boom. Behind the scenes, the technology relies on thousands of specialized computer chips. And in the coming years, they couldconsume immense amounts of electricity.

headline.main: A.I. Could Soon Need as Much Electricity as an Entire Country
headline.print_headline: A.I. Could Soon Need As Much Electricity As an Entire Country

docs.abstract: The further limits on shipments could cripple Beijing’s A.I. ambitions and dampen revenues for U.S. chip makers, analysts said.
docs.snippet: The further limits on shipments could cripple Beijing’s A.I. ambitions and dampen revenues for U.S. chip makers, analysts said.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Biden administration on Tuesday announced additional limits on sales of advanced semiconductors by American firms, shoring up restrictions issued last October to limit China’s progress on supercomputing and artificial intelligence.

headline.main: U.S. Tightens China’s Access to Advanced Chips for Artificial Intelligence
headline.print_headline: U.S. Adds Restrictions  On Chips  For China

docs.abstract: Researchers are transforming chatbots into online agents that play games, query websites, schedule meetings, build bar charts and do more.
docs.snippet: Researchers are transforming chatbots into online agents that play games, query websites, schedule meetings, build bar charts and do more.
docs.lead_paragraph: The widely used chatbot ChatGPT was designed to generate digital text, everything from poetry to term papers to computer programs. But when a team of artificial intelligence researchers at the computer chip company Nvidia got their hands on the chatbot’s underlying technology, they realized it could do a lot more.

headline.main: How ‘A.I. Agents’ That Roam the Internet Could One Day Replace Workers
headline.print_headline: ‘A.I. Agents’ Can Play Minecraft.  They’re Just Getting Warmed Up.
